cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) for constructing Intrusion Detection Systems (IDSs) for network data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of RL for packet sampling. The paper also discusses the use of RNNs, which are commonly used in machine learning, further supporting the likelihood of cs.LG. The paper's focus on IDSs and network data also suggests that cs.CR and cs.SI are likely categories. The use of neural networks and RL also suggests cs.NE and cs.AI as possible categories.
